column5: nice evening catch
WTG Roy...  Nice to see you getting out on the soft water  See you at Lakair...
Nice work Roy!
Very nice,  Good info there too. Reminder for me to add more info in my reports.  Thanks again
WTG Roy.  Nice looking fish.
Roy,nice looking walleye bud getting your fill before LaKair eh.See you soon.  Steve

OK Roy my neighbor I finally got my Soccer schedule for my kids with my wifes night out being tuesday I could be available for an evening fish trip with you if you need a partner one wednesday evening.My boat or yours  I am good with the net.  Thanks for the DORE report.MTP
Roy-  That must have been a blast pulling them up like that. Thanks for the info on how you did the magic. Keep smiling  Steven
Ok Mike, tomorrow night, (Wednesday) my place, my boat. I'll PM you instructions to get here.
what about me
Marc you know you never even need to ask.
hahahahah,Your a Gold hearted one Roy,gonna go see my dad and mom tomorrow night Tks kind one

A short report from last night on the Larry. I was out for 2 hours or so...5PM till 7. I got 6 for 6 then wrapped her up. The walleyes are on the feed. Smallest was 26" Took them all on a down deep husky jerk (blue and gold) 4'  behind a 2 ounce bottom bouncer. Surface temp was 61F. Was running 1.8 to 2.2 mph. upstream. Here's a pic of the one I brought home. (26")
Thats a great catch in a short time bud.And that smile.Between you and Lew,it,s a tough call to pick a winner.LOL  TFS fella.
SMILE !!!...who do you think you are...LEW ???  Brian beat me...
Roy. Whats with the Lew look? Didn't you know if you brought fish home you'd have to clean them??lol.  Great Report. Sounds like you know what you are doing!
LOL. I guess we were all thinking the same thing!

Good job Roy...I'm sure that one you brought home will be very happy there.  You have an aquarium big enough for him??? LOL  Lookin forward to seeing you up at Lakair....wow...just a few short weeks....
Smallest was 26"?, wow that's impressive. What was the biggest?
Beauty pickerel you got there.  Congrats!
They seemed to be all the same size Mike but I think the largest was 32".
Good job Roy.
That's gotta be at least 10lb's maybe more, that's amazing!
Thats great... someone will have to bring dinner to lakair...
Nice fish Roy,I have caught a couple of good sized Walleyes on the large deep down Husky but never thought about trolling one with a bottom bouncer. Joe
They won't go down deep enough consistently Joe, so the bottom bouncer keeps the bait in the strike zone. I'm only trolling 50' or so behind the boat.
Nice fish Roy, Congrats. Nice to see your getting out on the water and catching some nice fish. Thanks for the report.
....Good stuff Roy. Glad to see you getting your angling fix in before Lakair....*wink, wink*
Sweet fish hon, when's dinner.  Joey
Attaboy, Roy.  Trolling walleye in the propwash again?
I have to admit also, first thing I thought when I saw the pic was, smile, you're not Lew. Great outing Roy, that would sure put a smile on my face.
SWEEEEEET!!!!!!!!  Thats one nice CUE for the time out, and size wise, awesome. Post some pics of the aftermath also will ya, ie: dinner.
Nice Roy!   Still trying to find some in our area that are willing to bite.  Nice adaption of the bottom bounce....will have to remember that if I ever get a boat
Dat dere izza nice fishy Boudreaux! Too bat ya din take da pic of da 32"Wall-ice wif da logo in it for da Team 9... but dey is suckin' da hind twit anyway.
All those big fish in only two hours on the water?  Must belong to the fishermen's union.  Fish two hours and get paid a week of fish.
Nice catch Roy....  As for your smile...... It must be cause Lakair is just a week and change away..If that don't make ya smile I don't know what will...
Well done Roy!  Whopper
